'''Fellowship of the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence''' (abbreviated as '''AAAI Fellow''' or '''FAAAI''') is an award granted to individuals that the [[Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence]] (AAAI), judges to have made "significant, sustained contributions — usually over at least a ten-year period — to the field of [[artificial intelligence]]" (AI).<ref name=faaai>{{cite web|url=https://www.aaai.org/Awards/fellows-list.php|title=Elected AAAI Fellows|website=Aaai.org|accessdate=13 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=fellows>{{cite web|url=https://www.aaai.org/Awards/fellows.php|title=AAAI Fellows Program|website=Aaai.org|accessdate=13 November 2018}}</ref> Only a small percentage{{clarify|date=November 2018}} of members are nominated as [[fellow]]s.<ref name=nom/>

==Nominations==
Between 5 and 10 fellows are nominated annually (since 1990) by current AAAI members. {{As of|2018}} there are 2014 fellows in total, at the time of their nomination fellows have typically contributed to the field of AI for a decade or more after receiving their [[PhD]] or are at an equivalent career stage.<ref name=nom>{{cite web|url=https://www.aaai.org/Awards/fellows-letter.php|title=AAAI Fellows Nomination Letter|website=Aaai.org|accessdate=13 November 2018}}</ref> 

A partial list of fellows can be found in the [[:Category:Fellows of the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence|Category:Fellows of the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence]]. Some fellows use the [[post-nominal letters]] FAAAI.

