'''The College Fair''' is a U.S. based [[college]] and career planning technology company founded as '''Schoold''' in 2015 and based in [[San Francisco]], [[California]]. The College Fair app, launched in February 2016,<ref>{{cite web|title=College and Career Planning App Schoold Raises $4.5 Million|url=https://www.edsurge.com/news/2016-04-04-college-and-career-planning-app-schoold-raises-4-5-million|website=EdSurge|accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> helps individuals make informed decisions on choosing a college and major by compiling data from a variety of sources.

==History==
Schoold was co-founded by Sourabh Ahuja, who grew up in [[India]], and spent over 10 years as a Vice President developing mobile games at [[Glu Mobile]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sourabh Ahuja|url=http://schoold.co/profile-sourabh.html|website=Schoold|accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> Joe Ross serves on the San Mateo County Board of Education<ref>{{cite web|last1=Eslinger|first1=Bonnie|title=Joe Ross will be new face on San Mateo County education board|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2012/11/07/joe-ross-will-be-new-face-on-san-mateo-county-education-board/|website=The Mercury News|accessdate=4 October 2016}}</ref> and was previously the Chief Strategy Officer at [[HotChalk]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Joe Ross|url=http://schoold.co/profile-joe.html|website=Schoold|accessdate=4 October 2016}}</ref> The College Fair app seeks to democratize access to college search and counselling.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Shulman|first1=Robyn|title=Schoold: The Next Amazon for Education Opportunities, A Chat with CEO, Sourabh Ahuja|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/robyn-shulman-/schoold-the-next-amazon-f_b_11878720.html|website=The Huffington Post|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> Within the first month, the app surpassed 500,000 downloads.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hughes|first1=Carmen|title=Schoold Announces Successful Close of a $4.5 Million Seed Round|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/schoold-announces-successful-close-of-a-45-million-seed-round-300244659.html|website=PR Newswire|accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref>

==Funding==
The College Fair has received $4.5 million in [[seed capital]] from [[Social Capital (venture capital)|Social Capital]], FastForward Innovations, Learn Capital, and University Ventures.<ref name="VentureBeat">{{cite web|last1=Takahashi|first1=Dean|title=Schoold raises $4.5M and gets 500k downloads in 1st month for college-hunting app|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/04/01/schoold-raises-4-5m-and-gets-500k-downloads-in-1st-month-for-college-hunting-app/|website=VentureBeat|accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> In addition, [[Lorne Abony]] and [[Joseph Grundfest]] have contributed.<ref name="VentureBeat"/>

