'''The University Centre for Studies In Namibia''' ('''TUCSIN''') is a tertiary educational institution in [[Namibia]]. It is based in the [[Khomasdal]] suburb of the capital [[Windhoek]] and has campuses in [[Rehoboth, Namibia|Rehoboth]], [[Rundu]] and [[Oshakati]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Milestones |publisher=TUCSIN |url=http://www.tucsin.org/index.php/en/about/milestones |accessdate=3 June 2014}}</ref>
TUCSIN was co-founded by [[Beatrice Sandelowsky]] on 15 June 1978.<ref>{{cite news |title=Namibia: Beatrice Sandelowsky - a Decorated Archaeologist, Educationalist and Agitator for Equality (1943 ... ) |last=Mashuna |first=Timoteus |newspaper=[[New Era (Namibia)|New Era]] (via allafrica.com) |date=8 November 2013 |url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201311090184.html }}</ref> Since its inception it has trained 35,000 students and awarded over 1,000 bursaries to Namibian students. Andreas Wienecke is its current director.<ref>{{cite news |title=TUCSIN feiert 35-jähriges Bestehen |trans-title=TUCSIN celebrates 35th anniversary |language=German |date=17 June 2013 |url=http://www.az.com.na/bildung/tucsin-feiert-35-j-hriges-bestehen.410480 |newspaper=[[Allgemeine Zeitung (Namibia)|Allgemeine Zeitung]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Time-travelling with Tucsin |last=Repin |first=Lavrenty |newspaper=[[Windhoek Observer]] |date=1 August 2013 |url=http://observer24.com.na/national/2005-time-travelling-with-tucsin}}</ref>
