{{notability|Products|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox video game | collapsible = | state = | italic title = | title = Xanagrams | image = File:Xanagrams_cover.jpg | alt = | caption = | developer = Dean Software | publisher = Postern Ltd | series = | engine = | platforms = | released = 1984 | genre = [[Educational game|Educational]] | modes = }}
'''Xanagrams''' is an educational game that is a cross between a [[crossword puzzle]] and [[Scrabble]]. It was given away for free with the [[Amstrad CPC 464]] and was a very popular game.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amstrad CPC 464|url=http://www.retrogamer.net/profiles/hardware/amstrad-cpc-464/|website=Retro Gamer|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref> There are 3 difficulty level to the game, from middle school aged to adults. A game can consist of 1-5 words and the player is given a jumble of letters to sort out to form the correct words.{{cn|date=August 2016}}
